@DrWarrenFarrell: "...Lois Lane had no interest in Clark Kent, but she fell in love with Superman. Once she fell in love with Superman, she wanted Superman to be able to cry and express emotions. But the man who did cry, express emotions and feelings and was sensitive, Clark Kent, she has zero interest in."⁣
⁣
To watch more of this conversation about men and boys issues, parenting, mental health and relationships, click the link in my bio.⁣
⁣
Recorded 05/25/2021.

I share the story of Robert Crumb, an underground cartoonist, who was not only at the bottom of the male dominance hierarchy, but even further down on the female dominance hierarchy in terms of how desirable he was - that was until he became incredibly successful; In his own words: “That all changed when I got successful”.⁣
⁣
This episode went live on Monday on my YouTube channel, Apple Podcasts and Spotify.⁣ Click my bio link to watch more:
⁣
Recorded 05/25/2021.

@DrWarrenFarrell makes the case that the decline in boys IQ over the past 30 years - 15 points in total - is linked to fatherlessness.⁣
⁣
1 in 3 boys in the UK and the US grow up without a father. Boys are 50% more likely to fail than girls in the basic proficiency in any of the three core subjects: Reading, Math, and Science.⁣
⁣
To hear us talk more in-depth about these topics, head over to my YouTube channel and watch our conversation in full. Or, listen on Apple Podcasts or Spotify.⁣
⁣
Recorded 05/25/2021.
